---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'
---

<Layout
  title="Support"
  description="Help with Union — common questions, contact, and how to delete your account."
>
  <article class="prose-union">
    <h1 class="font-prayer text-5xl text-union-charcoal">Support</h1>

    <p class="mt-8 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      Union is a small product built by a small team. We read every
      email and try to reply within a couple of working days.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 font-prayer text-3xl text-union-charcoal">
      Email us
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      <a class="text-union-gold underline" href="mailto:hello@unionwith.app"
      >hello@unionwith.app</a>
      <span class="block text-base text-union-secondary">
        Bug reports, feature requests, prayer-corpus feedback, anything
        else — all welcome.
      </span>
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 font-prayer text-3xl text-union-charcoal">
      Common questions
    </h2>

    <h3 class="mt-6 font-ui text-xl font-medium text-union-charcoal">
      How do I delete my account?
    </h3>
    <p class="mt-2 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      In the app: Settings → Delete account. Type
      <code>delete</code> to confirm. Your account row, every
      check-in, every saved prayer, every reflection, and every
      related row are removed in a single transaction. We can&apos;t
      recover the data after — make sure you mean it.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-2 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      If you can&apos;t reach the app for some reason, email
      <a class="text-union-gold underline" href="mailto:hello@unionwith.app"
      >hello@unionwith.app</a>
      with the email address you signed up with and we&apos;ll delete
      it for you.
    </p>

    <h3 class="mt-6 font-ui text-xl font-medium text-union-charcoal">
      I&apos;m not getting the sign-in code email
    </h3>
    <p class="mt-2 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      Check your spam folder; the email comes from
      <code>noreply@mail.app.unionwith</code>. If it&apos;s not there
      after a few minutes, tap &ldquo;Use a different email&rdquo; on
      the sign-in screen and try again — there may have been a typo.
    </p>

    <h3 class="mt-6 font-ui text-xl font-medium text-union-charcoal">
      A prayer Union showed me has an error
    </h3>
    <p class="mt-2 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      Email us with the prayer&apos;s title and what&apos;s wrong.
      We&apos;ll review and fix it in the next update.
    </p>

    <h3 class="mt-6 font-ui text-xl font-medium text-union-charcoal">
      Can I export my saved prayers?
    </h3>
    <p class="mt-2 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      Not from the app yet — it&apos;s on the roadmap. In the
      meantime, email us and we&apos;ll send you a copy of the rows
      we hold for your account.
    </p>

    <h3 class="mt-6 font-ui text-xl font-medium text-union-charcoal">
      Is Union a counselling service?
    </h3>
    <p class="mt-2 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      No. Union helps you find prayers — it&apos;s a companion, not a
      counsellor, therapist, or pastor. If you&apos;re in crisis,
      please reach out to a qualified person or a crisis line in your
      country.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 font-prayer text-3xl text-union-charcoal">
      Crisis support
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      If you&apos;re struggling and need someone to talk to right now:
    </p>
    <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      <li>
        <strong>UK</strong> — Samaritans, free to call 24/7:
        <a class="text-union-gold underline" href="tel:116123">116 123</a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>US</strong> — 988 Suicide and Crisis Lifeline:
        <a class="text-union-gold underline" href="tel:988">988</a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Elsewhere</strong> — see
        <a
          class="text-union-gold underline"
          href="https://findahelpline.com"
          rel="external">findahelpline.com</a>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </article>
</Layout>
